import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend in wheat production over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wages', hue='year', kde=True, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wages over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wages')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby('year').mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data, ax=ax1, color='blue', label='Wheat Production')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wages', data=data, ax=ax2, color='red', label='Average Wages')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Wheat Production')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Average Wages')
    ax1.set_xlabel('Year')
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production and wages over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    corr = data.corr()
    sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wheat production and wages over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data[['year', 'wheat', 'wages']])
```
